Diagnosis.
Body length 5.0– 
7.5 mm
(
Figs. 1–2
). Pronotum with distinct tufts of black scales on either side of middle on anterior margin, laterally and on midline just anterior to midlength; width distinctly narrower than elytra at base, only very slightly wider than long. Femora each with 1 or 2 teeth, if 2 teeth then distal tooth poorly developed and very small. Elytra with concentrations of dark erect scales on intervals 3 and 5 near base and at about midlength. Male ventrite 5 (
Fig. 11
) with pair of small scale-tufted tubercles situated near basal margin; ventrite 1 longitudinally impressed medially and with pair of raised scale-tufted swellings on each side of midline at apical margin. Aedeagus (
Fig. 16
).
